The leader of the All Progressives Grand Alliance, APGA, in Abia State and member representing Aba South Constituency at the State House of Assembly, Hon Obinna Martins Ichita, has congratulated Professor Charles Soludo on the occasion of his inauguration as Governor of Anambra State. DAILY POST reported that Soludo was sworn in by the State Chief judge, Justice Onochie Anyachebelu at exactly 9:45 am, at the Anambra State Government House. The event was witnessed by several dignitaries, including the out-gone governor, Chief Willie Obiano and his wife, Mrs Ebelechukwu, and all the 30 members of the Anambra State House of Assembly. Reacting, Ichita, in a statement, on Thursday, while congratulating the new Anambra Governor, noted that Soludo’s emergence has opened a new chapter not only in Anambra State, but entire Igbo nation. He expressed the firm believe that Soludo’s values, exposure, experience and education will reflect on the quality of leadership the citizens shall experience in Anambra. According to Ichita, “In the face of all life threatening challenges and many legal hurdles that were on your way, the lord led by you and the people of Anambra to victory. “May the same lord keep and guide you as you have assumed office today as the new governor of Anambra state”. The Abia party leader further used the medium to congratulate the people of Anambra State and entire APGA family across Nigeria federation on another milestone achieved in deepening democracy in the southeast and entire Nigeria.